	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-12T06:35:18">International Personal Finance plc (IPF) is a United Kingdom-based holding company. IPF and its subsidiaries (the Group) are engaged in the provision of small sum, primarily home collected, short-term unsecured loans in emerging markets. The Company offers a digital product and an online digital credit service through hapi loans, in Poland. The Company operates using the Provident brand in eight countries, including Poland, the Czech Republic, Slovakia, Romania, Hungary, Mexico, Lithuania and Bulgaria. Its digital loan business operates in Finland, Estonia, Latvia, Australia and Lithuania with Credit24 and Sving brands. The Company's subsidiaries include IPF Holdings Limited, International Personal Finance Investments Limited, IPF International Limited, IPF Financing Limited, Provident Polska S.A., IPF Investments Polska Sp. z o.o., Provident Mexico S.A. de C.V., Provident Financial Romania IFN S.A., Provident Financial s.r.o. and Provident Financial Zrt., among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-20T14:30:59">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, International Personal Finance Plc revenues decreased 5% to L372.9M. Net income increased 70% to L26.9M. Revenues reflect Poland-Lithuania segment decrease of 13% to L137.3M, Czech/Slovakia segment decrease of 21% to L56.2M. Net income reflects Exceptional items decrease of 79% to L4.7M (expense), Impairment decrease of 14% to L112.6M (expense). Dividend per share increased from L0.04 to L0.05.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
